1
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:43,840
=No Pain No Gain=
(Adapted from the Qidian novel)

2
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:47,180
("Losing Money to Be a Tycoon"
by Qingshan Quzui)

3
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:50,220
=Episode 16=
(This story is purely fictional)

4
00:01:57,300 --> 00:01:58,550
- Off work!
- Off work!

5
00:01:58,550 --> 00:01:59,390
Off work.

6
00:01:59,940 --> 00:02:00,670
I'm leaving.

7
00:02:02,502 --> 00:02:03,390
See you tomorrow.

8
00:02:03,390 --> 00:02:03,830
Bye-bye.

9
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:04,470
Bye-bye.

10
00:02:04,470 --> 00:02:06,190
Lin Wan, I'm leaving first.

11
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:07,940
My neck's a bit stiff.

12
00:02:07,940 --> 00:02:09,191
I'm going to get a massage.

13
00:02:09,270 --> 00:02:10,110
Go ahead.

14
00:02:10,110 --> 00:02:11,300
Don't stay too late.

15
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:14,620
Leave early.

16
00:02:14,620 --> 00:02:16,350
Just leave the rest for tomorrow.

17
00:02:51,950 --> 00:02:53,390
Why are you alone?

18
00:02:53,990 --> 00:02:55,140
Where's your team?

19
00:02:55,140 --> 00:02:55,990
Hailu.

20
00:02:58,857 --> 00:03:00,110
The Divine Mountains and Seas

21
00:03:00,110 --> 00:03:01,790
finally got to move forward.

22
00:03:01,813 --> 00:03:03,270
The concept art needs detail checks,

23
00:03:03,270 --> 00:03:04,959
all the requirements
need to be finalized,

24
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,560
and I still have people
to coordinate with.

25
00:03:06,568 --> 00:03:09,350
Sky Fire is stirring things up,
saying we have no new games

26
00:03:09,350 --> 00:03:10,620
and that we've run out of ideas.

27
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:11,550
I just thought

28
00:03:11,550 --> 00:03:13,580
I should do more while I still can.

29
00:03:14,350 --> 00:03:16,110
You look really stressed.

30
00:03:16,420 --> 00:03:18,350
Don't carry everything by yourself.

31
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:22,740
Yeah, kind of.

32
00:03:24,835 --> 00:03:27,140
Even if the sky falls,
someone taller will hold it up.

33
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,860
Work never ends.

34
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:30,620
Once you're off the clock,
it's your own time.

35
00:03:30,620 --> 00:03:31,420
Come with me.

36
00:03:34,350 --> 00:03:35,350
Where are we going?

37
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:41,670
♪I can't wait until the weekend♪

38
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,030
♪Wanna see you right now♪

39
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,910
♪You never answer when I call you♪

40
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:50,510
♪Tell me what is that about♪

41
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:54,510
♪I heard you've been talking
about me again♪

42
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:57,220
♪I heard you coming back to me
in my dream♪

43
00:03:57,230 --> 00:03:58,070
Cheers.

44
00:03:58,510 --> 00:03:59,350
Cheers.

45
00:03:59,510 --> 00:04:00,390
Sugar-free.

46
00:04:03,580 --> 00:04:04,420
Hailu,

47
00:04:04,790 --> 00:04:05,740
I saw you

48
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:07,900
at a club before.

49
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:09,790
I didn't expect you
to be like this in private.

50
00:04:10,140 --> 00:04:11,620
I thought you were the type

51
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:13,580
who put work before everything,

52
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:14,620
steady,

53
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:16,180
and never makes mistakes.

54
00:04:17,350 --> 00:04:19,150
But being that kind of person
all the time

55
00:04:19,150 --> 00:04:20,150
is exhausting.

56
00:04:21,110 --> 00:04:22,670
One day, I realized

57
00:04:22,670 --> 00:04:24,790
everyone around me was praising me
for being capable,

58
00:04:24,790 --> 00:04:25,790
but no one cared

59
00:04:25,790 --> 00:04:27,470
how I became that way.

60
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:29,790
That's when it hit me.

61
00:04:30,060 --> 00:04:31,740
Work is for earning money.

62
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:33,300
Life is your own.

63
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:40,110
But

64
00:04:40,110 --> 00:04:42,300
your work style at Tengda

65
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,670
must be pretty happy, right?

66
00:04:44,300 --> 00:04:46,180
Where did you work before?

67
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:52,110
Do you really like Tengda?

68
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:53,060
I do.

69
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:55,150
I really, really, really do.

70
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:56,860
What if,

71
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:58,620
just hypothetically,

72
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:01,110
if one day, you found out

73
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:02,420
Tengda

74
00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:04,550
or Mr. Pei

75
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:06,300
wasn't the way you thought,

76
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:07,500
would you be disappointed?

77
00:05:10,180 --> 00:05:11,300
That's just a hypothetical.

78
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,620
Impossible.

79
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:15,550
By the way, did you know

80
00:05:15,550 --> 00:05:18,260
Sky Fire tried to poach us before?

81
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:19,391
I only wanted to find out

82
00:05:19,413 --> 00:05:21,110
what was going on,

83
00:05:21,110 --> 00:05:22,710
so I talked to a headhunter.

84
00:05:23,110 --> 00:05:24,740
And somehow,

85
00:05:24,857 --> 00:05:26,790
he ended up wanting
to join Tengda instead.

86
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:28,860
That's when I realized

87
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:30,670
Tengda really is that good.

88
00:05:30,990 --> 00:05:32,420
I don't think Mr. Pei would change.

89
00:05:33,110 --> 00:05:33,820
Do you?

90
00:05:34,990 --> 00:05:37,670
When he was at Sky Fire before,

91
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:39,500
I actually went to see him.

92
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:43,710
He was genuinely working there.

93
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:45,890
Like a normal employee.

94
00:05:45,890 --> 00:05:46,530
There's no way

95
00:05:46,530 --> 00:05:47,990
he went there to poach Wei, right?

96
00:05:48,170 --> 00:05:51,170
But after he came back,
he started acting strange.

97
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:54,820
Hailu, aren't you curious?

98
00:05:56,820 --> 00:05:58,670
I just need to do my job well.

99
00:05:58,670 --> 00:05:59,791
No need to be overly curious.

100
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:03,110
You're his special assistant.

101
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:04,230
You must know things

102
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:05,670
the rest of us don't, right?

103
00:06:07,940 --> 00:06:08,790
Lin Wan,

104
00:06:10,820 --> 00:06:12,470
don't take everything too seriously.

105
00:06:13,060 --> 00:06:15,260
Anyone can be different
from what you imagine.

106
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:17,030
Come on.

107
00:06:17,230 --> 00:06:18,060
Let's go dancing.

108
00:06:34,230 --> 00:06:36,420
If ride-hailing is off the table,

109
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,990
what else can I do to make money?

110
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,857
Do you need a designated driver?

111
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:46,420
Yes,

112
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:46,940
I do.

113
00:06:46,940 --> 00:06:48,420
Is your car over there? Follow me.

114
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:49,110
Slow down.

115
00:06:49,110 --> 00:06:50,380
Mister, need a designated driver?

116
00:06:50,380 --> 00:06:51,380
Okay. Let's go.

117
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:52,740
Mister, need a designated driver?

118
00:06:57,226 --> 00:06:59,420
(On Call Anytime)

119
00:07:14,180 --> 00:07:14,860
Hello?

120
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:16,150
Qian,

121
00:07:16,150 --> 00:07:17,590
I stayed up all night thinking,

122
00:07:17,590 --> 00:07:19,740
and I still couldn't find
a new blue ocean.

123
00:07:20,030 --> 00:07:21,550
Can you give me a bit more time?

124
00:07:21,820 --> 00:07:22,940
Sure. OK. No problem.

125
00:07:36,910 --> 00:07:37,470
Hello?

126
00:07:37,670 --> 00:07:38,380
Mr. Pei.

127
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:39,380
I've been thinking.

128
00:07:39,380 --> 00:07:40,724
The CEO Has an Exclusive Crush on You

129
00:07:40,724 --> 00:07:42,180
is Feihuang Pictures' first production.

130
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:44,346
The quality has to be solid
so we can build a reputation.

131
00:07:44,368 --> 00:07:45,790
So I want to hire the best team.

132
00:07:45,790 --> 00:07:46,910
Sure. OK. No problem.

133
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:54,180
Sure. OK. No problem.

134
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:57,910
Sure. OK. No problem.

135
00:07:59,620 --> 00:08:01,180
Sure. OK. No problem.

136
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,260
Hello?

137
00:08:08,302 --> 00:08:10,213
Mr. Pei, the character
promotional video sample

138
00:08:10,213 --> 00:08:11,524
for The Divine Mountains and Seas

139
00:08:11,524 --> 00:08:12,570
has been sent to your email.

140
00:08:12,591 --> 00:08:13,740
Did you check it?

141
00:08:13,740 --> 00:08:15,030
Can we approve it?

142
00:08:15,030 --> 00:08:16,420
Sure. OK. No problem.

143
00:08:16,420 --> 00:08:18,300
Sure. OK. No problem. Everything.

144
00:08:22,620 --> 00:08:23,820
What did Mr. Pei say?

145
00:08:24,470 --> 00:08:26,620
Sure. OK. No problem.

146
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:29,590
In one go again!

147
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:35,860
Who is it now?

148
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:36,900
Sir, where are you?

149
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:38,835
When will you arrive?
I've been waiting for ages.

150
00:08:38,835 --> 00:08:39,710
I'm so sorry.

151
00:08:39,768 --> 00:08:41,660
CC Designated Driving, at your service.

152
00:08:41,660 --> 00:08:42,500
Where are you?

153
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,380
Waiting by the roadside.

154
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:44,260
Right away.

155
00:08:48,260 --> 00:08:50,380
Lin Wan, your ideas really helped.

156
00:08:50,380 --> 00:08:52,140
My original design
was pretty conventional,

157
00:08:52,140 --> 00:08:53,946
but after drawing inspiration
from you guys,

158
00:08:53,946 --> 00:08:55,540
the characters became more distinctive

159
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:56,430
and really came to life.

160
00:08:56,430 --> 00:08:58,490
Like they grew straight
out of the ground naturally.

161
00:08:59,710 --> 00:09:00,230
Wait.

162
00:09:00,230 --> 00:09:01,310
Is that praise or an insult?

163
00:09:01,310 --> 00:09:02,950
Grew out of the ground, huh?

164
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:04,110
Come.

165
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:04,990
Tell me.

166
00:09:05,230 --> 00:09:05,830
This one.

167
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:08,380
(Wayfarer)

168
00:09:08,380 --> 00:09:10,540
This chubby guy is based on me, right?

169
00:09:10,568 --> 00:09:11,791
Why call him Wayfarer?

170
00:09:11,813 --> 00:09:15,140
This is the Divine Mountains and Seas,
and you still make me travel everywhere.

171
00:09:15,140 --> 00:09:16,380
That's too tragic.

172
00:09:16,380 --> 00:09:17,380
Are you targeting me?

173
00:09:18,710 --> 00:09:20,168
Sorry, Bao. I don't know why.

174
00:09:20,191 --> 00:09:22,710
But whenever I use you as inspiration,
I think of traveling.

175
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:24,190
Don't underestimate him.

176
00:09:24,190 --> 00:09:25,110
He's very strong.

177
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:31,260
(We want)

178
00:09:31,260 --> 00:09:33,380
(The Divine Mountains and Seas
to be an innovative)

179
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:35,260
(MMORPG (Massively Multiplayer
Online Role-Playing Game.)

180
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:38,230
(Players can switch between different
characters, explore the world,)

181
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:40,310
(and choose various classes
and strategies)

182
00:09:40,310 --> 00:09:41,500
(to challenge dungeons.)

183
00:09:42,140 --> 00:09:42,950
(For example,)

184
00:09:43,380 --> 00:09:44,620
(the Wayfarer)

185
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:45,740
(comes from the Orient.)

186
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:48,620
(He's a powerful mage)

187
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:51,500
(with a unique passive skill)

188
00:09:51,740 --> 00:09:54,500
(called The Unwilling Wayfarer.)

189
00:09:56,380 --> 00:09:58,740
(This skill shows)

190
00:09:58,740 --> 00:10:00,740
(that when he stands still,)

191
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:02,780
(he rapidly regenerates health and mana)

192
00:10:02,780 --> 00:10:05,350
(without using recovery items.)

193
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:10,710
(Once he moves,)

194
00:10:10,710 --> 00:10:12,620
(his health keeps dropping)

195
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:15,140
(while his rage meter keeps rising.)

196
00:10:15,140 --> 00:10:17,430
(When the rage bar is full,
he enters berserk mode.)

197
00:10:39,620 --> 00:10:40,620
Stand still to heal.

198
00:10:40,620 --> 00:10:41,740
Move to go berserk.

199
00:10:41,740 --> 00:10:43,020
That's literally me.

200
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:43,860
This is me!

201
00:10:44,350 --> 00:10:45,660
Let's look at the next one.

202
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:47,060
(Literati of the Wind)

203
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:49,260
Ruan Guangjian,

204
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:51,140
this character is based on you, right?

205
00:10:51,350 --> 00:10:52,020
That's cheating.

206
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:53,380
You made yourself so handsome.

207
00:10:54,350 --> 00:10:56,230
How is that cheating?

208
00:10:56,380 --> 00:10:57,310
Look at the name

209
00:10:57,310 --> 00:10:58,950
Lin Wan came up with.

210
00:10:58,950 --> 00:10:59,990
Literati of the Wind.

211
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:01,590
What a dashing name.

212
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:02,110
Of course,

213
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:03,350
he has to be handsome.

214
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:06,620
(Literati of the Wind)

215
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:08,260
(is a painter and calligrapher.)

216
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:10,860
(He's also a romantic swordsman.)

217
00:11:11,260 --> 00:11:13,230
(He pours his soul into his art,)

218
00:11:13,230 --> 00:11:14,860
(and lives a reclusive life.)

219
00:11:25,860 --> 00:11:28,590
(His weapon
is a giant calligraphy brush.)

220
00:11:28,990 --> 00:11:30,230
(Through wild strokes,)

221
00:11:30,230 --> 00:11:31,350
(he summons fierce winds.)

222
00:11:39,710 --> 00:11:41,860
"Mount Emei towers beyond
the Western heavens.

223
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:44,860
Mount Luofu stands intimately linked
to the Southern Sea.

224
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:48,900
With a stroke of my brush,
the great painter

225
00:11:49,260 --> 00:11:53,540
brings all the mountains and seas
into view."

226
00:12:05,940 --> 00:12:08,700
(Literati of the Wind)

227
00:12:08,991 --> 00:12:10,140
Wait, this isn't right.

228
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:11,350
Why does this character

229
00:12:11,350 --> 00:12:12,860
feel way stronger than mine?

230
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:13,860
Not really.

231
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:15,380
Every character has strengths

232
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:16,110
and weaknesses.

233
00:12:16,110 --> 00:12:17,470
They counter each other.

234
00:12:19,140 --> 00:12:20,740
But if we're talking about

235
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,168
the strongest one in this version...

236
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:25,710
It has to be...

237
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:26,940
(Guardian of Justice)

238
00:12:28,380 --> 00:12:29,380
I actually

239
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:30,860
spent the most time

240
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:32,380
designing this one.

241
00:12:33,140 --> 00:12:33,830
First,

242
00:12:33,830 --> 00:12:36,110
he's a tank.

243
00:12:36,110 --> 00:12:37,590
He shields

244
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:38,540
the team

245
00:12:38,540 --> 00:12:39,620
and takes on everything.

246
00:12:40,140 --> 00:12:41,020
Second,

247
00:12:41,020 --> 00:12:42,380
his passive skill

248
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:43,860
lets him rapidly increase defense

249
00:12:43,860 --> 00:12:45,590
when attacked.

250
00:12:45,590 --> 00:12:46,813
He also scatters gold coins

251
00:12:46,835 --> 00:12:48,190
that can damage enemies

252
00:12:48,190 --> 00:12:49,020
as an active skill.

253
00:12:49,380 --> 00:12:50,380
Finally,

254
00:12:50,380 --> 00:12:52,500
the ultimate move

255
00:12:52,860 --> 00:12:54,470
is called Self-Motivation.

256
00:12:55,990 --> 00:12:57,950
- Guardian of Justice.
- Guardian of Justice.

257
00:12:58,780 --> 00:13:00,470
The more I listen to the description,

258
00:13:00,470 --> 00:13:02,830
the more familiar it sounds.

259
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:06,190
Judging by the amount and speed
of coin-throwing,

260
00:13:06,191 --> 00:13:08,070
I think I already know
who this is based on.

261
00:13:09,820 --> 00:13:12,540
(Guardian of Justice)

262
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:56,740
Hello?

263
00:13:56,740 --> 00:13:58,260
Did you order a designated driver?

264
00:13:58,260 --> 00:13:58,900
I'm almost there

265
00:13:58,900 --> 00:13:59,900
after making a turn.

266
00:14:12,860 --> 00:14:13,470
Hello.

267
00:14:13,524 --> 00:14:15,950
Are you the author of
"The CEO Has an Exclusive Crush on You",

268
00:14:16,110 --> 00:14:16,620
Chit & Chat?

269
00:14:18,380 --> 00:14:19,190
I'm here.

270
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,430
Chit & Chat?

271
00:14:37,568 --> 00:14:38,780
What are you talking about?

272
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:40,070
Aren't you

273
00:14:40,070 --> 00:14:42,257
the author of
"The CEO Has an Exclusive Crush on You",

274
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:42,900
Chit & Chat?

275
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:43,990
We're supposed to meet here.

276
00:14:43,990 --> 00:14:45,110
What Chit & Chat?

277
00:14:45,110 --> 00:14:46,070
Are you crazy?

278
00:15:14,860 --> 00:15:15,540
Wu Sheng? Wu Xi?

279
00:15:17,110 --> 00:15:18,230
What are you doing here?

280
00:15:30,457 --> 00:15:31,660
What do you want to drink?

281
00:15:31,660 --> 00:15:32,350
My treat.

282
00:15:35,146 --> 00:15:36,190
- We are...
- We are...

283
00:15:36,190 --> 00:15:36,660
Chit...

284
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:37,350
And Chat...

285
00:15:51,780 --> 00:15:52,540
Right now.

286
00:15:52,540 --> 00:15:53,590
Now.

287
00:15:53,590 --> 00:15:54,990
I'll book you a ticket.

288
00:15:55,380 --> 00:15:56,380
Thank you, Mr. Pei.

289
00:15:56,524 --> 00:15:59,110
She misses home, and he books her flight
and gives her time off.

290
00:15:59,430 --> 00:16:01,430
What a lovely couple.

291
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,070
Sorry.

292
00:16:03,430 --> 00:16:04,190
Excuse us.

293
00:16:05,260 --> 00:16:06,540
Hero saving the beauty.

294
00:16:06,540 --> 00:16:07,430
They hold hands.

295
00:16:07,430 --> 00:16:09,620
A young and successful CEO,

296
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:11,590
and an independent and capable heiress.

297
00:16:11,590 --> 00:16:13,380
What a destined couple!

298
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,546
Wu Sheng, let's write a story
about Mr. Pei and Lin Wan

299
00:16:15,546 --> 00:16:16,590
Zhongdian Web Fiction.

300
00:16:18,990 --> 00:16:20,620
So you two are Chit & Chat?

301
00:16:20,620 --> 00:16:21,813
Why didn't you say so earlier?

302
00:16:21,990 --> 00:16:23,860
We didn't want Mr. Pei to find out

303
00:16:23,860 --> 00:16:25,830
that we wrote stories during work hours.

304
00:16:25,830 --> 00:16:27,500
No way. He'd definitely understand

305
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:28,660
and strongly support you.

306
00:16:32,310 --> 00:16:33,430
Sure. OK.

307
00:16:33,430 --> 00:16:34,540
No problem.

308
00:16:34,860 --> 00:16:35,500
See?

309
00:16:38,260 --> 00:16:39,140
He said OK.

310
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,500
We're colleagues here,

311
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,657
so I'll be straight with you.

312
00:16:43,740 --> 00:16:44,480
The main issue is

313
00:16:44,502 --> 00:16:46,260
that "The CEO Has
an Exclusive Crush on You"

314
00:16:46,260 --> 00:16:47,740
hasn't been able to find a screenwriter.

315
00:16:47,740 --> 00:16:49,235
The good ones are fully booked,

316
00:16:49,257 --> 00:16:50,500
and the not-so-good ones

317
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:51,500
are not so good.

318
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:52,900
So I wanted to ask

319
00:16:53,230 --> 00:16:55,110
if you two could adapt it yourselves.

320
00:16:57,235 --> 00:16:59,260
We have a friend
who works as a screenwriter.

321
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:01,260
He already lost his mind
after just a few years.

322
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:02,310
He says

323
00:17:02,310 --> 00:17:03,660
anyone who can read

324
00:17:03,660 --> 00:17:05,670
thinks they're qualified
to give suggestions.

325
00:17:05,768 --> 00:17:07,568
We're earning pretty well at Tengda.

326
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:09,540
Why would we put ourselves through
that kind of suffering?

327
00:17:09,546 --> 00:17:11,740
Besides, we were writing it
based on Mr. Pei...

328
00:17:11,791 --> 00:17:13,870
I mean, based on a very
well-matched pair of friends.

329
00:17:13,870 --> 00:17:15,740
We were writing it for fun. It's fictional.

330
00:17:16,430 --> 00:17:18,990
We just want to
make a bit of money off Mr. Pei.

331
00:17:18,990 --> 00:17:19,710
Yeah.

332
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:21,950
I see.

333
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:23,190
But it's really hard

334
00:17:23,430 --> 00:17:25,580
to find someone else.

335
00:17:27,740 --> 00:17:28,500
Huang,

336
00:17:28,740 --> 00:17:30,340
didn't you do some ghostwriting before?

337
00:17:30,670 --> 00:17:31,740
That

338
00:17:31,740 --> 00:17:32,500
Ma...

339
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,500
Ma Ma Ma Ma Ma, right?

340
00:17:34,813 --> 00:17:36,230
Ma Dubiao.
[*His pen name consists of five "Ma" characters]

341
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:38,580
Right, that's you.

342
00:17:38,910 --> 00:17:40,430
You've got writing experience.

343
00:17:40,430 --> 00:17:41,470
Why not write it yourself?

344
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:42,580
We'll authorize it.

345
00:17:42,791 --> 00:17:44,580
As long as the couple's name
for the leads

346
00:17:44,580 --> 00:17:45,910
stays "Qianyan Wanyu" .
[*So Much to Say]

347
00:17:45,910 --> 00:17:47,580
Yes, Qianyan Wanyu.

348
00:17:49,740 --> 00:17:51,780
Qianyan Wanyu?

349
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:58,260
(Mingyun Villa)

350
00:18:13,102 --> 00:18:13,870
Director Zhuang,

351
00:18:13,870 --> 00:18:14,946
let's have another drink.

352
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:18,630
Well, Mr. Pei...

353
00:18:18,702 --> 00:18:19,820
He just replied to the message.

354
00:18:19,820 --> 00:18:20,580
He's on the way.

355
00:18:20,580 --> 00:18:21,740
Traffic is terrible.

356
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:29,460
(Mingyun Villa)

357
00:18:29,470 --> 00:18:30,300
Hello, Mr. Pei.

358
00:18:33,591 --> 00:18:34,910
I'll park your scooter for you.

359
00:18:37,020 --> 00:18:39,150
This job is seriously affecting
my side job.

360
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:42,500
He's here.

361
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:43,670
I'm so sorry.

362
00:18:43,670 --> 00:18:45,020
Mr. Pei, let me introduce you.

363
00:18:45,020 --> 00:18:46,390
This is Mr. Pei.

364
00:18:46,390 --> 00:18:47,300
Mr. Pei Qian.

365
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:48,500
This is Director Zhuang Dace.

366
00:18:48,657 --> 00:18:49,710
Hello, Director Zhuang.

367
00:18:49,710 --> 00:18:50,920
I'm so sorry to keep you waiting.

368
00:18:50,924 --> 00:18:52,340
My last order was far away.

369
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:53,470
So I got delayed.

370
00:18:53,470 --> 00:18:54,430
Your last order?

371
00:18:55,950 --> 00:18:57,910
I mean, my previous workplace.

372
00:18:58,340 --> 00:19:00,430
I was at a meeting somewhere else.

373
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:01,190
Understandable.

374
00:19:01,190 --> 00:19:03,060
Sometimes my meetings
last a whole day too. Come.

375
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:03,910
Sit.

376
00:19:04,524 --> 00:19:05,470
Please have a seat.

377
00:19:11,580 --> 00:19:12,230
Sibo,

378
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:15,500
have you told Director Zhuang

379
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:16,990
about the project?

380
00:19:21,430 --> 00:19:22,710
I read

381
00:19:22,710 --> 00:19:23,470
the proposal

382
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:26,470
and the novel.

383
00:19:27,430 --> 00:19:28,150
The biggest issue

384
00:19:28,150 --> 00:19:30,060
with this project is

385
00:19:30,124 --> 00:19:31,702
that its overall vision is too limited.

386
00:19:31,740 --> 00:19:33,230
It lacks a strong hook.

387
00:19:34,470 --> 00:19:36,780
An ordinary sweet romance

388
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:39,340
is very hard to compete in the market.

389
00:19:41,780 --> 00:19:42,740
Director Zhuang,

390
00:19:42,740 --> 00:19:44,710
how can we make it competitive?

391
00:19:45,950 --> 00:19:48,470
There are three key points
for a TV series.

392
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:51,300
Pain point, emotional resonance,

393
00:19:51,546 --> 00:19:52,670
and discussion value.

394
00:19:52,950 --> 00:19:54,540
Content itself isn't the most important.

395
00:19:54,710 --> 00:19:56,540
The genre is.

396
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:58,470
The audience

397
00:19:58,470 --> 00:20:00,780
needs to feel emotional pain points

398
00:20:00,990 --> 00:20:02,990
and resonance.

399
00:20:02,990 --> 00:20:03,990
Pain points?

400
00:20:03,990 --> 00:20:05,780
Whose pain points? Resonating with whom?

401
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:07,580
I suggest

402
00:20:07,580 --> 00:20:08,870
turning this project

403
00:20:09,230 --> 00:20:10,580
into sci-fi.

404
00:20:10,990 --> 00:20:13,500
The grander the setting, the better.

405
00:20:13,710 --> 00:20:16,020
The larger the investment, the better.

406
00:20:16,150 --> 00:20:17,100
The production tier

407
00:20:17,100 --> 00:20:18,540
must be at least S+.

408
00:20:18,710 --> 00:20:20,190
There's no room left in the market

409
00:20:20,340 --> 00:20:22,740
for mid-tier shows now.

410
00:20:22,746 --> 00:20:23,880
And at minimum,

411
00:20:23,902 --> 00:20:25,870
shoot three seasons back-to-back.

412
00:20:34,260 --> 00:20:35,020
Director Zhuang,

413
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:36,680
the novel is called

414
00:20:36,702 --> 00:20:38,430
The CEO Has an Exclusive Crush on You.

415
00:20:38,430 --> 00:20:40,160
It doesn't seem big enough
for that scale.

416
00:20:40,260 --> 00:20:42,540
Maybe we should focus on

417
00:20:42,540 --> 00:20:44,190
telling a good romance story.

418
00:20:44,190 --> 00:20:46,020
The title is just a name.

419
00:20:46,020 --> 00:20:47,300
It can be changed anytime.

420
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,740
What matters is daring to be first.

421
00:20:49,991 --> 00:20:51,502
I've worked in TV for many years.

422
00:20:51,546 --> 00:20:52,950
I've seen it all.

423
00:20:52,950 --> 00:20:54,500
Sweet romance

424
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,260
has no future

425
00:20:55,260 --> 00:20:56,580
in today's market.

426
00:20:56,780 --> 00:20:58,260
It has to be a blockbuster.

427
00:20:58,540 --> 00:20:59,100
And

428
00:20:59,100 --> 00:21:00,540
it has to be sci-fi.

429
00:21:04,710 --> 00:21:06,500
Do you know the first book I read

430
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,630
after learning to read?

431
00:21:11,710 --> 00:21:13,390
UFO Fantasies.

432
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:17,100
Sci-fi is perfectly right up my alley.

433
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:18,670
It's what I feel most strongly about.

434
00:21:19,190 --> 00:21:20,990
We'll use the cutting-edge
filming techniques

435
00:21:20,990 --> 00:21:23,100
to open up a blue ocean

436
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:23,910
and be the first

437
00:21:23,910 --> 00:21:24,950
to break into this genre.

438
00:21:28,340 --> 00:21:29,580
Well, let me tell you this.

439
00:21:30,300 --> 00:21:32,670
I've even thought of the new title.

440
00:21:32,950 --> 00:21:33,630
Let's call it

441
00:21:33,630 --> 00:21:35,230
AI CEO:

442
00:21:35,230 --> 00:21:38,150
With You to the End of the Universe.

443
00:21:39,213 --> 00:21:40,060
How does that sound?

444
00:21:40,260 --> 00:21:41,060
Good?

445
00:21:41,540 --> 00:21:42,580
No problem, right?

446
00:21:43,470 --> 00:21:45,580
This is an artist's creative instinct.

447
00:21:45,791 --> 00:21:46,791
Nature calls.

448
00:21:46,791 --> 00:21:48,020
Mr. Pei, I drank several cups

449
00:21:48,020 --> 00:21:48,857
just waiting for you.

450
00:21:48,902 --> 00:21:49,791
You guys chat first.

451
00:21:53,740 --> 00:21:55,260
Mr. Pei, I think Director Zhuang seems

452
00:21:55,260 --> 00:21:56,260
a bit unreliable.

453
00:21:56,990 --> 00:21:58,950
Didn't I tell you to hire the best team?

454
00:21:59,540 --> 00:22:00,990
How did you end up with him?

455
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:03,190
Well,

456
00:22:03,190 --> 00:22:04,950
this is Feihuang's first show.

457
00:22:04,950 --> 00:22:06,190
We have to build a reputation.

458
00:22:06,190 --> 00:22:07,260
I looked for directors

459
00:22:07,260 --> 00:22:09,190
with notable works.

460
00:22:09,260 --> 00:22:11,670
I first contacted Director Zhao.

461
00:22:11,670 --> 00:22:12,780
He agreed at first,

462
00:22:12,780 --> 00:22:14,500
but then one of his shows blew up,

463
00:22:14,540 --> 00:22:15,500
and he backed out.

464
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:16,657
Didn't even reply to messages.

465
00:22:16,702 --> 00:22:17,324
Then...

466
00:22:18,430 --> 00:22:19,580
I tried this Director Liu.

467
00:22:20,860 --> 00:22:22,260
(Liu Wenyang)

468
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:24,340
This one?

469
00:22:24,340 --> 00:22:25,740
Douhua reviews say

470
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:26,990
he's even less reliable.

471
00:22:26,990 --> 00:22:27,540
Right?

472
00:22:27,540 --> 00:22:28,740
I think so too.

473
00:22:28,740 --> 00:22:30,870
But other directors
are even harder to book.

474
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:32,260
At least, Director Zhuang

475
00:22:32,390 --> 00:22:34,260
has an opening in his schedule.

476
00:22:34,260 --> 00:22:36,257
It's not like they have
tons of projects going on.

477
00:22:36,540 --> 00:22:37,740
Yeah.

478
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,190
If there's really no better choice,

479
00:22:41,768 --> 00:22:42,780
then it has to be him.

480
00:22:43,820 --> 00:22:44,540
Mr. Pei,

481
00:22:45,168 --> 00:22:46,540
but what Director Zhuang just said

482
00:22:46,540 --> 00:22:47,870
is completely different

483
00:22:47,870 --> 00:22:49,260
from the original novel.

484
00:22:49,260 --> 00:22:50,530
It's not the same story at all.

485
00:22:51,230 --> 00:22:51,910
Mr. Pei,

486
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:52,780
I went to the restroom,

487
00:22:52,780 --> 00:22:54,710
and suddenly my head was full of images.

488
00:22:54,710 --> 00:22:55,990
Inspiration just flooded in.

489
00:22:56,470 --> 00:22:56,990
Trust me.

490
00:22:56,990 --> 00:22:57,870
You must trust me.

491
00:22:57,870 --> 00:22:58,910
This project

492
00:22:58,910 --> 00:23:00,230
is going to be a huge success.

493
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:02,340
We just discussed it too.

494
00:23:02,340 --> 00:23:03,500
We hope that

495
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:05,870
as long as the core
of the original story is kept,

496
00:23:05,870 --> 00:23:08,470
we'll fully support
your creative direction.

497
00:23:13,990 --> 00:23:15,390
The TV industry

498
00:23:15,390 --> 00:23:17,630
needs bold, promising producers

499
00:23:17,630 --> 00:23:19,740
like you.

500
00:23:19,990 --> 00:23:21,740
I believe this project

501
00:23:21,740 --> 00:23:24,020
will leave a lasting mark

502
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:26,470
on television history.

503
00:23:28,340 --> 00:23:28,990
Well?

504
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:30,780
The producer has spoken.

505
00:23:30,780 --> 00:23:32,340
You must cooperate.

506
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:35,740
Mr. Pei,

507
00:23:35,990 --> 00:23:37,230
let me propose a toast.

508
00:23:38,820 --> 00:23:39,340
Sorry,

509
00:23:39,340 --> 00:23:40,430
I still have work later.

510
00:23:40,430 --> 00:23:41,950
If I drink alcohol, that'd be illegal.

511
00:23:42,260 --> 00:23:43,230
Illegal? How so?

512
00:23:43,910 --> 00:23:44,870
I'll drink tea instead.

513
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,740
Alright. Come on.

514
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:49,630
I'm suddenly feeling excited.

515
00:23:59,620 --> 00:24:03,700
(It's completely fine
to drink coffee and slack off at work)

516
00:24:17,470 --> 00:24:18,740
What's up, Huang?

517
00:24:18,990 --> 00:24:20,260
Taking a sauna?

518
00:24:20,260 --> 00:24:20,990
Mr. Ma.

519
00:24:22,470 --> 00:24:23,230
Nothing.

520
00:24:25,020 --> 00:24:25,950
Don't even ask.

521
00:24:25,950 --> 00:24:26,670
What happened?

522
00:24:26,990 --> 00:24:28,260
My project

523
00:24:28,260 --> 00:24:29,813
"The CEO Has an Exclusive Crush on You"

524
00:24:29,835 --> 00:24:31,260
already has a director attached.

525
00:24:31,260 --> 00:24:32,470
Isn't that a good thing?

526
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:34,190
I just finished an outline,

527
00:24:34,190 --> 00:24:36,500
and after the director read it,
he told me to start casting.

528
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:38,780
He said if we want this project to work,

529
00:24:38,780 --> 00:24:40,580
we need A-list actors.

530
00:24:41,990 --> 00:24:43,230
A-list?

531
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:44,100
I doubt this title

532
00:24:44,100 --> 00:24:45,820
can land A-listers.

533
00:24:46,060 --> 00:24:46,580
Oh, right.

534
00:24:46,580 --> 00:24:47,670
He changed the title too.

535
00:24:47,670 --> 00:24:48,500
That's better.

536
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:50,230
AI CEO:

537
00:24:50,230 --> 00:24:52,150
With You to the End of the Universe.

538
00:24:54,470 --> 00:24:55,020
It's fine.

539
00:24:55,230 --> 00:24:55,990
I'll help you.

540
00:24:55,990 --> 00:24:56,990
Don't stress.

541
00:24:58,020 --> 00:24:59,380
(General Manager's Office)

542
00:24:59,380 --> 00:25:01,540
We contacted so many agents.

543
00:25:01,950 --> 00:25:04,020
None of them is interested.

544
00:25:04,740 --> 00:25:05,500
Makes sense.

545
00:25:05,950 --> 00:25:07,260
Big-name actors

546
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:09,159
wouldn't be interested in a three-season

547
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:11,710
AI CEO: With You
to the End of the Universe, right?

548
00:25:11,780 --> 00:25:12,870
Don't you think

549
00:25:12,990 --> 00:25:14,060
the title sounds funny?

550
00:25:14,060 --> 00:25:15,390
Enough.

551
00:25:15,990 --> 00:25:17,910
There's actually one person
who's interested.

552
00:25:17,910 --> 00:25:18,500
Who?

553
00:25:19,950 --> 00:25:20,780
Lu Zhiyao.

554
00:25:21,260 --> 00:25:22,630
He's interested in the story?

555
00:25:23,670 --> 00:25:25,190
He's interested in the paycheck.

556
00:25:26,740 --> 00:25:28,260
His acting skills are terrible.

557
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:30,780
He's most famous for fighting
over the billing order, right?

558
00:25:31,990 --> 00:25:33,500
Is there anyone else?

559
00:25:36,260 --> 00:25:37,100
No.

560
00:25:39,340 --> 00:25:41,780
(Lu Zhiyao)

561
00:25:47,990 --> 00:25:48,740
Mr. Lu,

562
00:25:49,060 --> 00:25:49,910
and agents.

563
00:25:49,910 --> 00:25:50,870
His name is Tian.

564
00:25:51,670 --> 00:25:52,260
Tian.

565
00:25:52,500 --> 00:25:53,020
Mandy.

566
00:25:53,260 --> 00:25:54,430
We meet again.

567
00:25:55,260 --> 00:25:56,340
Mr. Huang,

568
00:25:56,710 --> 00:25:57,910
you know,

569
00:25:58,260 --> 00:25:59,740
Yao usually takes

570
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:00,950
film projects.

571
00:26:00,950 --> 00:26:02,500
He doesn't take TV series.

572
00:26:03,260 --> 00:26:04,820
But since we worked together

573
00:26:05,020 --> 00:26:07,190
quite pleasantly before,

574
00:26:07,670 --> 00:26:08,740
we're willing

575
00:26:08,740 --> 00:26:10,020
to give you this opportunity.

576
00:26:10,710 --> 00:26:11,340
Well,

577
00:26:11,710 --> 00:26:13,020
I'm so grateful for that.

578
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:15,990
Mr. Lu,

579
00:26:16,260 --> 00:26:17,780
have you read the proposal

580
00:26:17,780 --> 00:26:18,950
and story outline?

581
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:20,990
Any thoughts?

582
00:26:23,990 --> 00:26:24,990
We've read them.

583
00:26:25,430 --> 00:26:26,780
Yao feels that

584
00:26:26,780 --> 00:26:28,100
the story's point of view

585
00:26:28,260 --> 00:26:29,060
has a problem.

586
00:26:30,710 --> 00:26:31,500
Mr. Lu,

587
00:26:31,990 --> 00:26:32,990
please feel free

588
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:34,390
to speak your mind.

589
00:26:39,670 --> 00:26:41,300
The core of AI CEO

590
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:43,150
is the CEO.

591
00:26:44,020 --> 00:26:45,950
But your perspective
starts from the female lead.

592
00:26:45,950 --> 00:26:46,910
That doesn't make sense.

593
00:26:47,500 --> 00:26:49,300
Romance isn't the focus.

594
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:50,990
The focus should be

595
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:52,390
on the CEO's growth arc

596
00:26:52,390 --> 00:26:56,020
and how he eventually governs
the entire universe.

597
00:26:56,540 --> 00:26:57,260
Hold on.

598
00:26:58,260 --> 00:27:00,300
Why would the CEO govern the universe?

599
00:27:04,020 --> 00:27:05,990
Romance as the theme is too narrow.

600
00:27:07,150 --> 00:27:08,540
This is sci-fi.

601
00:27:08,540 --> 00:27:11,430
Sci-fi must explore
the mysteries of the universe.

602
00:27:13,724 --> 00:27:15,020
A.I. Artificial Intelligence.

603
00:27:15,670 --> 00:27:16,500
Have you seen that?

604
00:27:17,500 --> 00:27:19,340
The protagonist's image
fits me perfectly.

605
00:27:20,035 --> 00:27:21,580
You can use that as a reference.

606
00:27:21,580 --> 00:27:23,100
Haven't you seen it, Mr. Huang?

607
00:27:24,300 --> 00:27:25,150
It's our friend.

608
00:27:25,150 --> 00:27:26,430
Judy acted in it.

609
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:28,910
People online say that Mr. Law
looks a lot like Yao.

610
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:31,340
You should get him to star
in the remake.

611
00:27:31,340 --> 00:27:32,300
- That works.
- Yeah.

612
00:27:32,300 --> 00:27:32,990
Makes sense.

613
00:27:32,990 --> 00:27:33,670
Yeah.

614
00:27:33,990 --> 00:27:35,150
The fan forums

615
00:27:35,150 --> 00:27:36,340
say the same, right?

616
00:27:36,340 --> 00:27:37,230
- Exactly.
- Right.

617
00:27:37,230 --> 00:27:38,060
Yeah.

618
00:27:42,150 --> 00:27:43,060
Jude Law?

619
00:27:45,740 --> 00:27:46,500
Pay attention.

620
00:27:46,710 --> 00:27:48,190
(This boy is named Handsome.)

621
00:27:48,190 --> 00:27:50,470
(He's the world's
first emotional robot.)

622
00:27:50,470 --> 00:27:53,190
(But he looks no different
from a real human.)

623
00:27:53,190 --> 00:27:55,870
(Even the way he talks and behaves
is just like a person.)

624
00:27:58,540 --> 00:28:01,300
(By the bridge, willows drape a stream.
Your home is just west of North Bridge.)

625
00:28:01,300 --> 00:28:02,180
(AI CEO: With You
to the End of the Universe)

626
00:28:03,910 --> 00:28:05,260
We all read the script.

627
00:28:05,346 --> 00:28:07,390
First, there are problems
with the story's core logic.

628
00:28:07,740 --> 00:28:08,500
Second,

629
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:10,300
the character doesn't have depth.

630
00:28:10,346 --> 00:28:12,870
In the first six episodes,
there's nothing to hook the audience.

631
00:28:13,150 --> 00:28:14,540
Once you lose those hooks,

632
00:28:14,540 --> 00:28:16,540
I'm skeptical whether this show

633
00:28:16,540 --> 00:28:17,820
can go the distance.

634
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:21,300
What are your thoughts about
the first six episodes in particular?

635
00:28:21,300 --> 00:28:23,230
The beginning is pretty engaging.

636
00:28:23,990 --> 00:28:25,100
But later on,

637
00:28:25,100 --> 00:28:26,540
the plot just keeps repeating itself.

638
00:28:27,340 --> 00:28:29,430
The writer probably
didn't think it through.

639
00:28:29,540 --> 00:28:30,020
He...

640
00:28:30,020 --> 00:28:30,500
Mandy.

641
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:33,300
Look, the script keeps recycling
the same thing.

642
00:28:33,300 --> 00:28:34,670
The whole story runs on plot armor.

643
00:28:34,670 --> 00:28:37,146
It gets tiring. How is the actor
supposed to act this out?

644
00:28:37,168 --> 00:28:39,060
Plus, the early setup
and later story direction

645
00:28:39,060 --> 00:28:40,150
are completely disconnected.

646
00:28:40,150 --> 00:28:41,740
Sci-fi is too niche.

647
00:28:41,820 --> 00:28:43,300
Not niche at all.

648
00:28:43,500 --> 00:28:44,430
To be honest...

649
00:28:44,430 --> 00:28:45,670
Director, excuse me.

650
00:28:47,500 --> 00:28:48,500
Hello, Director Wang?

651
00:28:49,060 --> 00:28:50,430
Hi.

652
00:28:50,430 --> 00:28:51,430
Yes, I'm Mandy.

653
00:28:51,580 --> 00:28:53,300
We read your script,

654
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,260
and I have a few thoughts.

655
00:28:55,340 --> 00:28:56,300
First,

656
00:28:56,300 --> 00:28:57,740
there are some problems

657
00:28:57,740 --> 00:28:58,990
with the story's core logic.

658
00:28:58,990 --> 00:28:59,670
Second,

659
00:28:59,670 --> 00:29:00,791
in the first six episodes,

660
00:29:00,791 --> 00:29:02,630
the character doesn't have depth.

661
00:29:02,630 --> 00:29:04,080
There's nothing to hook the audience.

662
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:05,990
The beginning is pretty engaging.

663
00:29:05,990 --> 00:29:08,470
But later on, the plot
just keeps repeating itself.

664
00:29:08,780 --> 00:29:11,430
The whole story runs
on plot armor. It gets tiring.

665
00:29:11,430 --> 00:29:13,390
Plus, the earlier setup
and the later story direction

666
00:29:13,390 --> 00:29:14,500
are completely disconnected.

667
00:29:15,190 --> 00:29:16,990
Pure love is still too niche.

668
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:19,150
Wait.

669
00:29:19,150 --> 00:29:19,990
She's talking

670
00:29:19,990 --> 00:29:21,430
about our show, isn't she?

671
00:29:21,670 --> 00:29:24,390
No, but everything she said
is exactly the same.

672
00:29:25,780 --> 00:29:27,430
Actually, after thinking it over,

673
00:29:27,500 --> 00:29:29,670
I feel our story might work better

674
00:29:29,670 --> 00:29:30,950
as a mysterious fantasy.

675
00:29:33,740 --> 00:29:35,910
Have you seen Game of Thrones?

676
00:29:36,260 --> 00:29:36,990
Yes.

677
00:29:38,150 --> 00:29:39,740
I want to make something like that.

678
00:29:43,300 --> 00:29:44,910
(Pay attention. This handsome lad)

679
00:29:44,910 --> 00:29:46,740
(is a security guard from the North.)

680
00:29:46,740 --> 00:29:47,820
(One day,)

681
00:29:47,820 --> 00:29:49,340
(he runs into a White Walker.)

682
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:52,300
Does he even know
what he's talking about?

683
00:29:52,430 --> 00:29:53,780
Game of Thrones is fantasy,

684
00:29:53,780 --> 00:29:54,780
not mysterious fantasy.

685
00:29:55,540 --> 00:29:58,300
(By the bridge, willows drape a stream.
Your home is just west of North Bridge.)

686
00:29:59,340 --> 00:30:00,870
Demon Lord of the North:

687
00:30:01,060 --> 00:30:03,230
I Love Only You for Three Lifetimes.

688
00:30:07,150 --> 00:30:08,150
Great title.

689
00:30:08,546 --> 00:30:10,500
Sibo revised this
for several nights straight.

690
00:30:10,500 --> 00:30:11,780
All based on your feedback.

691
00:30:11,780 --> 00:30:13,060
Look, he's exhausted.

692
00:30:13,060 --> 00:30:14,150
You see,

693
00:30:14,300 --> 00:30:15,230
we can't just make shows

694
00:30:15,230 --> 00:30:17,190
for ourselves these days.

695
00:30:17,740 --> 00:30:19,430
We have to watch market trends.

696
00:30:19,430 --> 00:30:19,990
Right.

697
00:30:20,150 --> 00:30:22,260
I saw fan feedback

698
00:30:22,910 --> 00:30:24,870
saying there's too much
mysterious fantasy.

699
00:30:25,540 --> 00:30:27,150
Audiences are tired of it.

700
00:30:27,580 --> 00:30:28,740
Should we

701
00:30:28,740 --> 00:30:30,300
upgrade the script again

702
00:30:30,820 --> 00:30:32,300
and make it fantasy instead?

703
00:30:34,540 --> 00:30:35,500
Think about it.

704
00:30:37,991 --> 00:30:40,060
(Pay attention. This handsome lad
is called Monkey.)

705
00:30:40,146 --> 00:30:41,670
(He started at the grassroots level.)

706
00:30:41,724 --> 00:30:43,919
(He once served as supervisor
at the Heavenly Stables,)

707
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:45,968
(later deputy director
of the Celestial Peach Garden.)

708
00:30:45,968 --> 00:30:47,060
(Due to a work mistake,)

709
00:30:47,060 --> 00:30:49,699
(he was reassigned to Mount Five-Finger
for geological research,)

710
00:30:49,700 --> 00:30:52,070
(and led the quest for
the scriptures in Journey to the West.)

711
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:56,580
Finished!

712
00:30:56,910 --> 00:31:02,190
I finally finished writing it!

713
00:31:05,820 --> 00:31:08,700
(By the bridge, willows drape a stream.
Your home is just west of North Bridge.)

714
00:31:14,670 --> 00:31:17,190
Why isn't she picking up?

715
00:31:23,020 --> 00:31:23,990
Hello, Mandy?

716
00:31:24,300 --> 00:31:26,020
I'm waiting at our private kitchen.

717
00:31:26,020 --> 00:31:27,020
When are you arriving?

718
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:28,540
I'm sorry, Mr. Huang.

719
00:31:29,190 --> 00:31:30,150
Yao's new movie

720
00:31:30,150 --> 00:31:31,260
is about to be released.

721
00:31:31,346 --> 00:31:33,435
He's shifting away
from being a hyped celebrity now,

722
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:34,670
so this project

723
00:31:34,670 --> 00:31:36,230
doesn't fit his future career plan.

724
00:31:36,430 --> 00:31:37,710
He won't be taking the role.

725
00:31:37,710 --> 00:31:38,540
Sorry about that.

726
00:31:38,670 --> 00:31:40,635
I have another call coming in.
Talk to you later.

727
00:31:40,990 --> 00:31:41,430
Mandy...

728
00:31:41,630 --> 00:31:41,950
Mandy!

729
00:31:41,950 --> 00:31:43,260
You can't do this, Mandy.

730
00:31:55,902 --> 00:31:57,740
What's going on? Are they coming or not?

731
00:31:59,990 --> 00:32:01,150
Are they coming or not?

732
00:32:03,020 --> 00:32:04,430
Lu Zhiyao dropped out.

733
00:32:07,190 --> 00:32:08,390
The show business

734
00:32:09,150 --> 00:32:10,670
is way too ruthless.

735
00:32:12,724 --> 00:32:14,724
(Supreme Mage of the North Continent
Still Loves You)

736
00:32:22,230 --> 00:32:22,820
Fine.

737
00:32:24,300 --> 00:32:25,190
Another one gone.

738
00:32:28,060 --> 00:32:30,670
I worked like a dog,

739
00:32:30,670 --> 00:32:33,230
writing day and night,

740
00:32:33,230 --> 00:32:35,150
and he didn't show up.

741
00:32:35,340 --> 00:32:36,340
He dropped out?

742
00:32:36,910 --> 00:32:38,020
Mr. Pei,

743
00:32:38,020 --> 00:32:40,740
we can't start filming now.

744
00:32:40,740 --> 00:32:42,780
We can't start filming?

745
00:32:44,580 --> 00:32:45,470
Sibo.

746
00:32:45,470 --> 00:32:47,150
When are we starting production?

747
00:32:47,150 --> 00:32:48,910
Sibo.

748
00:32:49,670 --> 00:32:51,020
Calm down, Sibo.

749
00:32:51,020 --> 00:32:51,780
There's no need

750
00:32:51,780 --> 00:32:53,540
to put all our eggs in one basket.

751
00:32:53,540 --> 00:32:54,260
If he can't come,

752
00:32:54,260 --> 00:32:55,950
we'll switch male leads.

753
00:32:55,950 --> 00:32:57,670
We can't, Mr. Pei.

754
00:32:57,670 --> 00:32:58,540
We can't?

755
00:32:58,540 --> 00:32:59,740
There's no one left.

756
00:32:59,740 --> 00:33:01,990
If we replace him,
it'll be a completely new face.

757
00:33:02,820 --> 00:33:04,150
New faces are great.

758
00:33:04,820 --> 00:33:05,950
That's great.

759
00:33:06,430 --> 00:33:08,260
Who says unknown actors
can't attract viewers?

760
00:33:08,260 --> 00:33:09,780
Acting skills are what really matter.

761
00:33:11,702 --> 00:33:14,020
I actually have a promising candidate
with big dreams.

762
00:33:14,020 --> 00:33:14,670
Who?

763
00:33:14,670 --> 00:33:16,870
The one who pitched himself
at DreamForge Capital.

764
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:17,740
His name is Shi Huo.

765
00:33:17,740 --> 00:33:18,540
Shi Huo?

766
00:33:18,950 --> 00:33:20,780
He's not famous

767
00:33:21,300 --> 00:33:23,060
and hasn't done any serious roles.

768
00:33:23,740 --> 00:33:25,710
But at least he won't try
to rewrite the script.

769
00:33:25,710 --> 00:33:27,230
What's the female lead's name again?

770
00:33:27,230 --> 00:33:27,870
Mo Shan.

771
00:33:27,870 --> 00:33:29,300
Would she be willing to act with him?

772
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:29,950
Yes.

773
00:33:30,100 --> 00:33:30,870
Definitely.

774
00:33:30,870 --> 00:33:31,390
Listen.

775
00:33:31,390 --> 00:33:33,430
After what happened
with that frigging Lu Zhiyao,

776
00:33:34,910 --> 00:33:36,430
Mo Shan texted saying

777
00:33:36,430 --> 00:33:38,635
she'd even act with me as the made lead
if she had to.

778
00:33:39,670 --> 00:33:40,670
Then it's settled.

779
00:33:40,990 --> 00:33:42,630
Shi Huo it is.

780
00:33:42,910 --> 00:33:43,780
Everything

781
00:33:44,300 --> 00:33:46,470
is the best possible arrangement.

782
00:33:48,300 --> 00:33:49,500
Sibo,

783
00:33:49,540 --> 00:33:51,020
your hair

784
00:33:51,060 --> 00:33:52,150
and that beard

785
00:33:52,150 --> 00:33:53,230
need some trimming.

786
00:33:53,230 --> 00:33:54,870
You look like a caveman.

787
00:33:55,430 --> 00:33:57,740
(You have a new order.
Please process it.)

788
00:33:57,740 --> 00:33:58,820
(Instant Order)

789
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:01,060
I need to be somewhere else.

790
00:34:01,060 --> 00:34:01,670
I'll get going.

791
00:34:01,670 --> 00:34:02,230
Alright.

792
00:34:09,020 --> 00:34:10,660
When did so many people get here?

793
00:34:10,660 --> 00:34:12,940
(Shenhua International)

794
00:34:12,940 --> 00:34:13,910
(DreamForge Capital)

795
00:34:13,910 --> 00:34:14,950
New face?

796
00:34:17,580 --> 00:34:18,620
How new is he?

797
00:34:19,750 --> 00:34:20,540
Director,

798
00:34:20,750 --> 00:34:22,390
to be honest, I've never seen him.

799
00:34:22,390 --> 00:34:24,270
I heard from Mr. Ma,
he's extremely unknown.

800
00:34:24,380 --> 00:34:25,102
Like no one knows.

801
00:34:25,540 --> 00:34:27,060
Will it work?

802
00:34:27,060 --> 00:34:28,220
I don't know.

803
00:34:28,946 --> 00:34:30,580
Hello, Director Zhuang.
Hello, Mr. Huang.

804
00:34:30,580 --> 00:34:31,140
Mr. Ma.

805
00:34:31,310 --> 00:34:31,990
This actor

806
00:34:31,990 --> 00:34:34,270
is here to audition
for the male lead role.

807
00:34:34,750 --> 00:34:35,580
Shi Huo.

808
00:34:37,540 --> 00:34:38,270
Which one?

809
00:34:41,220 --> 00:34:41,910
Hey.

810
00:34:41,910 --> 00:34:42,790
Where is he?

811
00:34:46,180 --> 00:34:47,020
Uh...

812
00:34:52,180 --> 00:34:53,180
Okay.

813
00:34:53,180 --> 00:34:54,180
Stop. That's enough.

814
00:34:54,180 --> 00:34:55,270
Very good.

815
00:34:55,270 --> 00:34:56,140
Well, mister,

816
00:34:56,140 --> 00:34:57,830
could we have a word?

817
00:34:57,910 --> 00:34:59,100
On stage, please.

818
00:35:04,140 --> 00:35:05,220
Hello, sirs.

819
00:35:05,830 --> 00:35:06,620
Everyone.

820
00:35:07,180 --> 00:35:08,180
Over here.

821
00:35:09,660 --> 00:35:11,430
And those in the distance.

822
00:35:11,430 --> 00:35:12,470
Hello, everyone.

823
00:35:13,660 --> 00:35:14,700
My name is Shi Huo.

824
00:35:14,700 --> 00:35:16,620
My dream is to be truly famous.

825
00:35:16,750 --> 00:35:18,140
I want everyone to know

826
00:35:18,140 --> 00:35:19,620
that I am an actor.

827
00:35:20,140 --> 00:35:21,750
Please remember my name.

828
00:35:22,430 --> 00:35:24,180
Shi Huo!

829
00:35:24,180 --> 00:35:25,140
Good. Very good.

830
00:35:25,140 --> 00:35:25,660
Excellent.

831
00:35:25,660 --> 00:35:27,660
Please begin.

832
00:35:27,660 --> 00:35:28,350
Okay.

833
00:35:29,990 --> 00:35:30,700
Director,

834
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:31,750
what should I do?

835
00:35:31,750 --> 00:35:33,100
Just do a random bit.

836
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:33,990
No problem.

837
00:35:47,700 --> 00:35:50,020
What is this supposed to mean?

838
00:35:51,060 --> 00:35:52,220
I'm holding a horse.

839
00:35:55,100 --> 00:35:55,910
Anything else?

840
00:35:55,910 --> 00:35:56,660
Yes.

841
00:36:03,390 --> 00:36:05,140
And this one?

842
00:36:05,750 --> 00:36:06,830
I'm lifting the curtain,

843
00:36:06,946 --> 00:36:08,470
waiting for the princess to step up.

844
00:36:10,140 --> 00:36:10,950
Anything else?

845
00:36:11,390 --> 00:36:13,470
I have a more emotional performance.

846
00:36:13,620 --> 00:36:14,750
Let me get into the mood.

847
00:36:29,430 --> 00:36:30,950
Does he need that long?

848
00:36:31,390 --> 00:36:32,500
You can start.

849
00:36:33,270 --> 00:36:34,390
I'm done, Director.

850
00:36:36,830 --> 00:36:38,580
What is this scene about?

851
00:36:40,390 --> 00:36:42,270
I'm standing with ten thousand soldiers,

852
00:36:42,270 --> 00:36:44,660
watching the protagonist leave.

853
00:36:50,443 --> 00:36:52,140
Any other candidates here?

854
00:36:53,430 --> 00:36:54,270
Director,

855
00:36:54,910 --> 00:36:57,700
maybe you should talk to Lu Zhiyao again.

856
00:37:04,500 --> 00:37:05,140
Well done.

857
00:37:05,990 --> 00:37:06,830
Very well done.

858
00:37:07,620 --> 00:37:09,060
You're cast.

859
00:37:10,430 --> 00:37:11,180
Director,

860
00:37:11,620 --> 00:37:12,620
did I hear that right?

861
00:37:12,620 --> 00:37:13,700
Are you serious?

862
00:37:13,700 --> 00:37:16,220
You're the next Lu Zhiyao.

863
00:37:16,390 --> 00:37:18,180
You'll be even more famous.

864
00:37:18,180 --> 00:37:19,180
Shi Huo. Truly famous.

865
00:37:33,620 --> 00:37:35,310
I'll report to Mr. Pei.

866
00:37:40,220 --> 00:37:40,950
Hello?

867
00:37:40,950 --> 00:37:42,310
Did you order a designated driver?

868
00:37:42,430 --> 00:37:43,220
Please wait a moment.

869
00:37:43,220 --> 00:37:45,140
I'm 500 meters away.

870
00:37:45,620 --> 00:37:46,430
Designated driver?

871
00:37:47,470 --> 00:37:48,180
What?

872
00:37:48,180 --> 00:37:50,430
What the heck is all this?

873
00:37:54,540 --> 00:38:00,380
♪The moonlight kisses the balcony♪

874
00:38:03,260 --> 00:38:08,580
♪The clouds cause trouble for no reason♪

875
00:38:10,180 --> 00:38:14,540
♪Glittering lights all drift away♪

876
00:38:14,540 --> 00:38:18,740
♪Shadows intertwine, row by row♪

877
00:38:18,740 --> 00:38:22,260
♪Endless laughter♪

878
00:38:23,340 --> 00:38:29,300
♪The storm is coming♪

879
00:38:37,820 --> 00:38:40,940
♪The stars sigh♪

880
00:38:42,140 --> 00:38:44,780
♪Surrounded by neon lights♪

881
00:38:48,140 --> 00:38:52,380
♪Stacking up dreams
into a sail accidentally♪

882
00:38:52,540 --> 00:38:56,900
♪Courage blows the waves off the bay♪

883
00:38:56,900 --> 00:39:01,220
♪Stars ablaze, lights dim and scattered♪

884
00:39:01,220 --> 00:39:05,540
♪Only my lone shadow remains♪

885
00:39:05,980 --> 00:39:08,660
♪Who overturned my fairytale ship?♪

886
00:39:25,620 --> 00:39:34,300
♪The evening breeze
stirs restless unease♪

887
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:39,540
♪Dark clouds scatter across the beach♪

888
00:39:41,260 --> 00:39:45,740
♪The little sailboat secretly departs♪

889
00:39:45,740 --> 00:39:51,820
♪The ocean in the dream remains unseen♪

890
00:39:51,820 --> 00:39:55,980
♪Only waiting♪

891
00:39:55,980 --> 00:39:59,140
♪Fills the distant shore♪

892
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:06,300
♪Even the stranded light
still feels warm♪

893
00:40:06,300 --> 00:40:10,540
♪Turning into a brighter lighthouse♪

894
00:40:10,540 --> 00:40:14,580
♪It's only another return to shore♪

895
00:40:14,860 --> 00:40:18,620
♪No longer lonely♪

896
00:40:20,300 --> 00:40:24,540
♪This is my fairytale ship♪
